Wilson and Goff ... the first and last for the average intended air yards on passing charts. I also split it for the pocket time. Russell was never intercepted below 2.5sec.

#nflverse - inspiration: @benbbaldwin https://t.co/4DPSi17YcR

The distribution of touchdowns for pocket time. 
I think we overestimate time. It doesn't take 4 seconds for a great pass and it often depends on the quarterback's style.

#nflverse https://t.co/IQzycDGtMe

Burrow was in the last positions by the number of play action. I want to believe that Zach Taylor protected him because of the o-line. With Karras, Cappa and Collins I believe and hope that we will see many more as for Herbert. And then we see them in the conf final #nflverse https://t.co/2ZFBbXDFjs
